The paper presents a formal model of HSA and uses the Event-B language for development and verification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the development and verification of concurrent software applications and HSA-compliant platforms, which could fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories, respectively. The paper also mentions the use of proofs and testing for verification, which could be relevant to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
